                    <h2>PRIVACY RULES FOR NOVEL</h2>
                    <h3>A.	ABOUT FORMAT:</h3>
                    <p style="white-space: pre-line">
1. Story chapter includes main chapter and sub-chapter. Main chapters have Arabic numerals or Roman numerals; or type in alphabetical order. Sub-chapters are chapters that are not numbered in the above order. For example: Chapter Beginning/End, Intersection, Afterword, Sub-Chapter, Chapter numbered in decimal as 1.5, etc. In case the author does not use the above method for numbering, all chapters are defaulted to main chapter.

2. Composed stories must be presented in Vietnamese with correct spelling. Absolutely do not use hybrid languages that do not belong to formal literary standards such as teencode, acronyms, emojis, abuse of Chinese words, Japanese suffixes/honorifics such as -chan, -kun, -san …, do not use foreign languages if not necessary, …

3. Stories must be presented according to common typing rules and Vietnamese punctuation standards.
                    </p>
                    <h3>B. ABOUT CONTENT:</h3>
                    <p style="white-space: pre-line">
4. The audience is mainly aimed at Vietnamese youth/teens, so they are not allowed to promote deviant, unethical, or illegal acts of Vietnam.

5. The story must be self-composed, including the plot, setting, and characters, etc., originally created by the author himself. It is strictly forbidden to use or borrow plots, backgrounds, or characters, etc. from official works, published, or posted online. It is strictly forbidden to copy or plagiarize other authors' stories in any form. Authors who violate this will have their accounts permanently banned.

6. It is only allowed to refer to, or install details, contexts, or characters, etc. (Easter egg), or write parody in works under Article 6 when not mentioning the main thing. identify the name of the character, the name of the object, the name of the place, or the name of the work, etc.; or in works in the public domain (public domain) such as legends, myths, fairy tales, legends, etc. Violations of Article 6 shall be counted as violations of Article 5.

7. Do not post fanfics about real or fictional characters, or reuse the setting of any other stories not owned by you. It is strictly forbidden to mention real historical figures in Vietnam.

8. Do not write content that is offensive, libelous or distorts any real individual, organization, group, religion or party unless the author can prove the consent of the party. and certified by that party.

9. Don't pull reads in fraudulent forms such as abusing the 18+ warning, attaching tags that are not in the content of the story, deleting old chapters and reposting them, posting unfinished chapters, spamming the name or link of the story. In many places on Bookie, naming or choosing a cover photo is misleading.
                    </p>
                    <h3>C. ABOUT IMAGES AND RELATED ISSUES:</h3>
                    <p style="white-space: pre-line">
10. The author has the right to use and edit all images including self-produced images or images sourced on the internet to make story covers, book covers.

11. All other illustrations such as characters, places, objects, etc. in the story must be produced by the author himself, hired to produce, or produced from non-copyrighted sources. Upon request, the author must demonstrate the right to use these images. Bookie is not responsible if a dispute occurs. Absolutely do not abuse illustrations! Requires thorough understanding of the subject matter illustrated before applying.

12. All images used as covers or illustrations must be aesthetically pleasing, not vulgar or sensitive.
                    </p>

                    <h3>D. ABOUT STORY SUBSCRIPTION:</h3>

                    <p style="white-space: pre-line">
13. Within the first 2 hours from the time of publishing the story, the author must publish 2000 words, and within 7 days must publish at least 10,000 words (excluding sub-chapters). When the quota of 10,000 words is not completed within the above 7 days, the story will be banned because of overdue approval.

14. Each main chapter must be at least 2,000 words. Sub-chapters have a free word count.

15. Stories that violate regulations D13, D14, if not edited after receiving a reminder comment within 2 hours, will be removed without notice on the regulation page.
                    </p>


                    <h3>E. ABOUT STORY MANAGEMENT:</h3>

                    <p style="white-space: pre-line">
16. Absolutely do not cause controversy or incite controversy in other authors' stories in any form.

17. Respect your readers. If there are any comments that need to be appealed, please contact the Board of Directors to be resolved.

18. When operating within the Bookie community site, absolutely do not link or quote links to other reading websites in any form.

19. The genres of short stories will be reviewed according to the above law and consider more elements of content, artistry and humanity, focus on plot, character depth, language and leadership. Funny and satirical stories are also considered. Long stories will also be censored by the Board of Directors according to regulations. Stories that do not meet the standards will be banned.

20. Any form of circumvention based on things not mentioned in the law will be handled by the Board of Directors at its sole discretion to create a premise later.

 

Rules will always be updated to suit the current orientation and status of the site, so authors are required to regularly monitor. All stories that do not have comments from the Board of Directors are in a state of waiting for approval, please stay calm and wait.


